name: Amundi Fixed Maturity 2027 German Bund Government Bond UCITS ETF Dist
description_en: The Amundi Fixed Maturity 2027 German Bund Government Bond UCITS ETF Dist seeks to track the FTSE German Government 2027 Maturity index. The FTSE German Government 2027 Maturity index tracks German government bonds. The index does not reflect a constant maturity range (as is the case with most other bond indices). Instead, only bonds that mature during the designated year (here: 2027) are included in the index. Rating: AAA. Maturity: December 2027 (the ETF will be closed afterwards). The ETF's TER (total expense ratio) amounts to 0.09% p.a.. The Amundi Fixed Maturity 2027 German Bund Government Bond UCITS ETF Dist is the only ETF that tracks the FTSE German Government 2027 Maturity index. The ETF replicates the performance of the underlying index by full replication (buying all the index constituents). The interest income (coupons) in the ETF is distributed to the investors (Semi annually). The Amundi Fixed Maturity 2027 German Bund Government Bond UCITS ETF Dist is a very small ETF with 6m Euro assets under management. The ETF was launched on 25 April 2024 and is domiciled in Luxembourg. Show more Show less

name: BNP Paribas Easy MSCI Japan Min TE UCITS ETF USD
description_en: The BNP Paribas Easy MSCI Japan Min TE UCITS ETF USD seeks to track the MSCI Japan Select Filtered Min TE index. The MSCI Japan Select Filtered Min TE index tracks large and mid cap stocks from Japan. The stocks included are filtered according to ESG (environmental, social and corporate governance) and climate change criteria. The index also aims to minimize the tracking error relative to the parent index (MSCI Japan). The ETF's TER (total expense ratio) amounts to 0.16% p.a.. The BNP Paribas Easy MSCI Japan Min TE UCITS ETF USD is the only ETF that tracks the MSCI Japan Select Filtered Min TE index. The ETF replicates the performance of the underlying index by full replication (buying all the index constituents). The dividends in the ETF are accumulated and reinvested in the ETF. The BNP Paribas Easy MSCI Japan Min TE UCITS ETF USD is a very small ETF with 2m Euro assets under management. The ETF was launched on 19 April 2024 and is domiciled in Luxembourg. Show more Show less

name: Amundi Lifecycle 2030 UCITS ETF Acc
description_en: The Amundi Lifecycle 2030 UCITS ETF Acc seeks to track the FTSE Lifecycle 2030 Screened Select index. The FTSE Lifecycle 2030 Screened Select index tracks a portfolio of developed market equities, EUR denominated government bonds and EUR denominated corporate bonds. The weights of the different asset classes are adjusted over time with equities being weighted less and bonds more as the date specified in the index name approaches. After the target date has been reached, the index tracks a portfolio of short-term EUR denominated government bonds (time to maturity: max. 1 year). The securities included are filtered according to ESG criteria (environmental, social and corporate governance). Rating of the bonds included: investment grade. The ETF's TER (total expense ratio) amounts to 0.18% p.a.. The Amundi Lifecycle 2030 UCITS ETF Acc is the only ETF that tracks the FTSE Lifecycle 2030 Screened Select index. The ETF replicates the performance of the underlying index by full replication (buying all the index constituents). The dividends in the ETF are accumulated and reinvested in the ETF. The Amundi Lifecycle 2030 UCITS ETF Acc is a very small ETF with 6m Euro assets under management. The ETF was launched on 28 January 2025 and is domiciled in Luxembourg. Show more Show less
